JOHANNESBURG - Thokoza in Ekurhuleni was brought to a standstill on Monday morning when some residents took to the streets.It was estimated that about 4,000 residents shut down Khumalo Street, using rocks and burning tyres demanding a new hostel be built to accommodate them.READ: Protests continue as Ennerdale residents awaits MashatileThey say a new hostel was promised to them, back in 1994. Residents of neighbouring townships have now joined in the protest.eNCA